CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 14, 1962, pg. A2 reads: "Key Clubs - The Key Club, a junior service organization affiliated with the Kiwanis Club, last week-end attended the Pennsylvania district convention held in Hilton Hotel, Pittsburgh. Over 1,250 boys were assembled to learn new techniques and projects for the Key Clubs which they represent... Right photo [left photo]: Arthur Kaplan, president of the Westinghouse High School Kay Club; James Brown, vice president, Westinghouse; Robert Riband, secretary; A.G. (Terry) Shafer, Pennsylvania district commander, and P.D. Mitchell, Williamsport, chairman of the Key Clubs relations. - Harris Photo.".Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Group of Key Club members, from left:  Arthur Kaplan, James Brown, Robert Riband, A.G. (Terry) Shafer, and P.D. Mitchell, standing in front of Williamsport High School banner in Hilton Hotel
